<p>After trying to sort onChange of a dropdown menu, records should be sorted by "column_name" in the DB ASC, but for some reason they're getting out of order. I'm running an afterFind method that decrypts the data and the values are all fine but the ordering isn't as expected.</p>  <p>With the code below, when I select an option (also the table column) "name", then it should order: apple, banana, cat, dog.</p>  <p>But when I choose an option that is encrypted value (also the column name) "purpose", it orders: apple, cat, banana, dog. </p>  <p><strong>Controller</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>$this-&gt;Paginator-&gt;settings = array(             'limit'=&gt;100,             'contain' =&gt; false,             'conditions' =&gt; $conditions,             'order' =&gt; $model.'.'.$field.' '.$order         );         $results = $this-&gt;Paginator-&gt;paginate(); </code></pre>  <p><strong>Model</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>public function afterFind($results = array(), $primary = false) {     foreach ($results as $key =&gt; &amp;$val) {         if (isset($val['Model'])) {             $this-&gt;decryptFields($val['Model'], $this-&gt;fieldsToEncrypt());         }     }      return $results; }  private function fieldsToEncrypt() {     return array(         'someField'     ); } </code></pre>  <p>Thx, shon</p>